							Inventory
						



Quick Ship (643)
									
									

New to LightingDirect (86)
									
									





Special FeaturesWe have pointed out some special features that exist in this category. ENERGY STAR fixtures are tested by the EPA and are certified to use less energy, saving you money and also helps protect the environment.  ADA COMPLIANT fixtures (wall mount only) have been approved by the American's with Disabilities Act requiring the fixture extend no more than 4" from the wall.
CONVERTIBLE fixtures are supplied with chain or stems along with optional hardware for flush mounting to the ceiling without the use of the chain or additional stems. 
COVERED Fixtures are chandeliers with a decorative glass or fabric shade that cover the light arms.

							Special Features
						



ADA Compliant (139)
									
									





Light DirectionDetermines where the light is mostly directed.  Ambient Lighting means that the light is not focused in any one direction. Up / Down Lighting fixtures direct light in both the up and downward position. Up or Down fixtures have the option of being mounted in either the up or down position. Bath Bar Fixtures are sometimes called Vanity Strip Lights and do not point up or down, but rather illuminates out in all directions. Please see examples below.

							Light Direction
						



Ambient Lighting (337)
									
									

Down Lighting (165)
									
									

