Putting this in perspective, for the first nine months of the (27:55) subscription revenue grew 26%, and now comprises 81% of total revenue. And during the same period, SaaS revenue has grown over 500% and now comprising 17% of total revenue.
As I mentioned earlier, we are seeing a substantial increase in volatility in our search business, driven by the market dynamics which are out of our control. What this means is that part of our business, the non-core, non-subscription and non-SaaS business, has very little visibility, and consequently, future revenue from search is quite uncertain.
While it is impossible to know or predict the full impact of this, it is likely to have an impact on our top line, though to what extent we are still trying to model. That said, given the success of our revenue diversification strategy, and the fact that our key areas of growth are firing on all cylinders, I feel confident that we should be able to mitigate some of this impact, and we will continue to test new strategies and report more on this over the coming quarters.
